@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "The Journey Forward";
    ViewData["MetaDescription"] = "MaximoRO development update covering the Level 35 handoff, Pathfinder and Kafra improvements, English localization, secure accounts, and the upcoming Level 35-50 experience.";
}

<section class="page-hero news-page-hero journey-forward-hero">
    <div class="container page-hero-content">
        <div class="eyebrow">
            <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
            July 23, 2026 &middot; Development Update
        </div>

        <h1>
            The journey
            <span>forward.</span>
        </h1>

        <p>
            A clearer road beyond the beginner route, stronger in-game
            support, a more English-friendly client, safer account creation,
            and the first design work for MaximoRO's Level 35-50 experience.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="btn hero-primary-button" href="#progression">
                Progression Update
            </a>

            <a class="btn hero-secondary-button" href="#client-and-website">
                Client and Website
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section news-page-section" id="update-overview">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="centered-heading section-heading">
            <div class="eyebrow">
                <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
                One day, several connected systems
            </div>

            <h2>
                Building a smoother
                <span>MaximoRO journey.</span>
            </h2>

            <p>
                This development update separates work that is live on the
                website, work implemented in the game-server project, client
                packages prepared for runtime testing, and the Level 35-50
                route now entering design and audit work.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card-grid">
            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">01</span>

                <h3>Implemented</h3>

                <p>
                    Pathfinder dialogue, support Kafras, reset services, and
                    Academy referrals are implemented in the game project.
                    Verified registration and deployment safeguards are now
                    live on the website.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card featured-card">
                <span class="feature-number">02</span>

                <h3>Ready for QA</h3>

                <p>
                    Complete English Tipbox and map-entry localization packages
                    have passed structural validation and are ready for careful
                    client runtime testing.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">03</span>

                <h3>In progress</h3>

                <p>
                    The next phase of the player experience is being traced from Level 35
                    through Level 50, including second-job advancement and the
                    transition into normal Ragnarok progression.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section world-section" id="progression">
    <div class="container world-grid">
        <div class="world-panel">
            <img
                class="world-image"
                src="/images/news/journey-forward-pathfinder.jpg"
                alt="A Pathfinder helping a new adventurer choose the road ahead" />
        </div>

        <div class="world-content">
            <div class="eyebrow">
                <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
                New-player progression
            </div>

            <h2>
                A clearer road
                <span>through Level 35.</span>
            </h2>

            <p>
                The beginner journey now has a more deliberate beginning,
                middle, and conclusion. Players are introduced to the
                Pathfinder after their first job change, receive repeatable
                access to guidance, and leave Assignment III with clear next
                steps instead of reaching a silent progression cliff.
            </p>

            <ul class="world-list">
                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Academy registration now introduces the Pathfinder route
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Pathfinder menus return safely after guidance and assignments
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Assignment labels now read consistently as I, II, and III
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Assignment III completion explains what to pursue after Level 35
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Players are directed toward training, second jobs, travel,
                    class guidance, and the Build Adviser
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Existing assignment requirements and rewards remain unchanged
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section news-page-section" id="support-network">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-heading-row">
            <div class="section-heading">
                <div class="eyebrow">
                    <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
                    Pathfinder support network
                </div>

                <h2>
                    Guidance and services,
                    <span>where players need them.</span>
                </h2>

                <p>
                    The main Pathfinder now stands beside the Build Adviser in
                    Prontera, while an Izlude copy preserves the Academy and
                    Swordsman route. Supporting Kafra employees have also been
                    placed throughout the beginner network.
                </p>
            </div>

            <a class="text-link"
               asp-controller="Guides"
               asp-action="Pathfinder">
                Open the Pathfinder guide
                <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
            </a>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card-grid">
            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">01</span>

                <h3>Prontera hub</h3>

                <p>
                    The primary Pathfinder and Build Adviser now form one
                    discoverable support hub in Prontera. Izlude remains
                    supported for the Academy and Swordsman journey.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card featured-card">
                <span class="feature-number">02</span>

                <h3>Full Kafra services</h3>

                <p>
                    Route Kafras can provide save points, storage, guild
                    storage, cart rental, town travel, Pathfinder travel,
                    and beginner training-area transportation.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">03</span>

                <h3>Beginner-friendly travel</h3>

                <p>
                    Training-area travel is free through Base Level 60, while
                    town and support-hub travel use clear, controlled Zeny
                    prices that preserve normal world travel.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">04</span>

                <h3>Stat and skill resets</h3>

                <p>
                    The Build Adviser now supports both stat and skill resets.
                    Eligible beginner jobs receive free service through Base
                    Level 60, with a paid option for later progression.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card featured-card">
                <span class="feature-number">05</span>

                <h3>Reset safeguards</h3>

                <p>
                    Skill resets verify inventory weight and attached class
                    systems such as carts, mounts, falcons, wargs, dragons,
                    and Mado Gear before making changes.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">06</span>

                <h3>Second-job audit</h3>

                <p>
                    Existing second-job routes are now being mapped before the
                    Level 35-50 experience is designed, so new guidance works
                    with Ragnarok's advancement systems rather than bypassing them.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section world-section" id="client-and-website">
    <div class="container world-grid">
        <div class="world-content">
            <div class="eyebrow">
                <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
                Client localization
            </div>

            <h2>
                More of Rune-Midgarts,
                <span>readable in English.</span>
            </h2>

            <p>
                Two large localization packages were prepared from the exact
                2026 client data. They preserve current IDs, links, icons,
                navigation targets, map behavior, and non-text fields while
                replacing Korean player-facing text.
            </p>

            <ul class="world-list">
                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    1,503 Tipbox articles preserved
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    3,053 Tipbox title and page fields translated
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    1,198 map-entry records preserved
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    2,630 map-entry localization fields translated
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Zero Korean fields remain in either prepared payload
                </li>

                <li>
                    <span>◆</span>
                    Both packages remain in runtime QA and are not yet announced as live
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="world-panel">
            <img
                class="world-image"
                src="/images/news/journey-forward-localization.jpg"
                alt="MaximoRO scholars reviewing maps and guidebooks during localization work" />
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section news-page-section" id="account-and-operations">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="centered-heading section-heading">
            <div class="eyebrow">
                <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
                Website and account systems
            </div>

            <h2>
                Safer registration,
                <span>steadier deployment.</span>
            </h2>

            <p>
                Mandatory email verification is now part of the live account
                flow. The same work also strengthened registration feedback,
                protected Production secrets, corrected a form blocker, and
                made successful publishing depend on local and public health
                checks.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card-grid">
            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">01</span>

                <h3>Verification required</h3>

                <p>
                    New accounts are created in an unconfirmed state and unlock
                    only after the player follows a secure, expiring email link.
                    Verification tokens are stored as hashes.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card featured-card">
                <span class="feature-number">02</span>

                <h3>Secure Gmail delivery</h3>

                <p>
                    Gmail SMTP is configured with TLS and an app password. The
                    sender credentials remain outside the repository and are
                    loaded into the Production process from the local secret
                    store.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">03</span>

                <h3>Verification safeguards</h3>

                <p>
                    Hashed expiring tokens, resend throttling, fail-closed email
                    configuration, automatic schema setup, and dedicated verify
                    and resend pages protect the account flow.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">04</span>

                <h3>Registration unblocked</h3>

                <p>
                    An invisible anti-spam field was corrected after it
                    unintentionally blocked legitimate submissions. Real
                    players can now pass validation and reach account creation.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card featured-card">
                <span class="feature-number">05</span>

                <h3>Clearer form feedback</h3>

                <p>
                    Invalid fields now appear in one visible summary, focus
                    moves to the first problem, and valid submissions display
                    a clear Creating Account state while the request is running.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="feature-card">
                <span class="feature-number">06</span>

                <h3>Reliable publishing</h3>

                <p>
                    Website deployment now uses isolated staging, verified
                    process shutdown, backup and rollback support, Production
                    secret validation, and local plus public checks that require
                    registration to be available.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>

        <div class="news-development-panel">
            <div>
                <div class="eyebrow">
                    <span class="server-status-dot"></span>
                    Registration status
                </div>

                <h2>Verified registration is live.</h2>

                <p>
                    The public registration form is enabled, Production is
                    loading its protected sender settings, and deployment
                    health checks are passing. A real inbox registration remains
                    the final delivery test for the configured Gmail sender.
                </p>
            </div>

            <a class="btn hero-primary-button"
               asp-controller="Home"
               asp-action="Register">
                Create Account
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="final-cta-section" id="next">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="final-cta-panel">
            <div class="final-cta-emblem">M</div>

            <div class="final-cta-content">
                <div class="eyebrow">
                    Next focus
                </div>

                <h2>The Level 35-50 experience.</h2>

                <p>
                    The next step is to shape the journey from Pathfinder
                    graduation into second-job advancement and normal world
                    progression. That work begins with a careful audit of
                    existing routes, requirements, trials, rewards, and
                    possible progression gaps before new content is added.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="final-cta-actions">
                <a class="btn hero-primary-button"
                   asp-controller="Home"
                   asp-action="ProgressionPatch">
                    Previous Progression Patch
                </a>

                <a class="btn hero-secondary-button"
                   asp-controller="Home"
                   asp-action="News">
                    Return to News
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
